@startuml journey-guardian
' ============================================================
' Zoomed User-Experience Flow: Guardian + Admin Surface
'
' Product/UX-clarity altitude for the parent-facing console (route tree
' "/guardian"). Node fill: white = shipped, rose = planned (not yet built).
' The approve action is admin-only (ADR-005); guardians can monitor but a
' guardian cannot self-approve (API returns 403).
'
' Source screens:
'   frontend/src/router.tsx  (guardian route tree: /guardian/*; a single AdultGate
'     wraps the whole adult subtree -- both /guardian and /admin -- ADR-014)
'   frontend/src/auth/AdultGate.tsx  (ADR-014: one kid-to-adult boundary crossing,
'     warm state in sessionStorage, 5-min TTL, parked on entering kid mode)
'   frontend/src/guardian/LoginPage.tsx, ConsolePage.tsx (family console)
'   frontend/src/admin/AdminConsolePage.tsx (review queue), admin/ReviewDetailPage.tsx
'   frontend/src/guardian/IntakePage.tsx, ProfilesPage.tsx, AssignChildrenDialog.tsx
'   frontend/src/guardian/RequestsPage.tsx  (/guardian/requests: approve/decline
'     a child's story request, WS-B; shipped -- guardian-own-family or
'     admin-global, NOT admin-only like the ADR-005 storybook approval gate)
'   frontend/src/guardian/BooksPage.tsx  (/guardian/books: catalog browse +
'     assign, WS-E; guardian-only nav entry)
'   docs/planning/adr/adr-005-mandatory-human-approval.md
'   docs/planning/adr/adr-014-device-authorized-kid-access.md (single AdultGate
'     boundary; role-based post-login redirect)
'   Phase 4a mobile UI wireframe concept spec (PR #47, shipped; the source doc under
'     docs/superpowers/specs/ was retired as scratch output once its work merged)
' ============================================================

title Guardian + Admin Surface Journey\n("/guardian"; rose = planned. Approve is admin-only, ADR-005)

skinparam defaultFontName "Roboto"
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam roundCorner 10
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #5a3e28
skinparam ArrowFontColor #5a3e28
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #FFFDF8
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #8c6f56
skinparam ActivityDiamondBackgroundColor #f8f3e8
skinparam ActivityDiamondBorderColor #8c6f56
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #F1E9D8
skinparam NoteBorderColor #c9b48f
skinparam swimlaneWidth same

|#CDDCEC|Guardian|
|#C5D9CC|Admin|
|#E4E4E4|System|

|Guardian|
start
:Sign in
(email/password or Google,
Apple if the flag is on);
note right: /guardian/login  •  shipped\nADR-014 -- conditional now: only a cold entry\nor a step-up crossing UP from kid mode reaches\nthis (or the "Grown-ups only" password re-entry);\nadult<->adult navigation is free once warm
:Land on the Console
(role-based: admin-only -> /admin;\nguardian-only or dual-role -> /guardian);
note right: AdultGate + ProtectedRoute  •  shipped

' --- Setup: profiles ---
:Add or edit a child's profile
(name + preset avatar);
note right: /guardian/profiles  •  shipped

' --- Request a story ---
:Open Story requests,
review my child's idea
(screened text + flags);
note right: /guardian/requests  •  shipped\n(guardian-own-family or admin-global;\nNOT admin-only, unlike the approval gate below)
:Set age band, length,
optional series title,
then Approve or Decline;
note right: shipped  •  approve builds a Concept\nand enqueues generation

:Request a story from Intake
("Who's it for?", topic, tone);
note right: /guardian/intake  •  shipped
:Watch "My Requests"
show "Generating...";
note right: intake job status  •  shipped

|System|
:Write the story, then
run the safety check;
note right: generation + validator gate  •  shipped\ndetail: seq-generation

' --- Approval gate (admin-only, ADR-005) ---
|Admin|
repeat :pick the top of the queue;
  :Open the review queue
  (Flagged, then Ready,
  then Still processing);
  note right: /admin  (Review queue)  •  shipped\n(the review queue moved here from the guardian console)
  :Open a story: flagged passages
  first, then the full text
  with flags highlighted inline;
  note right: /admin/review/:storybookId  •  shipped
backward:Send back with a note
-> the story is rewritten;
repeat while (Safe for a child?) is (no) not (yes -> approve)
:Approve
(recorded human gate, ADR-005.
Guardians get 403 here);

' --- Assign ---
|Guardian|
:Assign the approved story
to the child it was for;
note right: assign  •  shipped
if (Give it to siblings too?) then (yes)
  :"Assign more" -> pick more
  children (adds only the new ones);
  note right: AssignChildrenDialog  •  shipped
else (no)
endif
:The child's avatar now shows
"new story ready!";
note right: crosses to the kid surface
stop

legend bottom
  |= Node |= Meaning |
  |<back:#FFFDF8>  white  </back>| Shipped in the guardian console today |
  |<back:#F3D9D4>  rose   </back>| Planned, not yet built |
  Columns: <b>Guardian</b> (request + assign + monitor; the console also has a
  notification bell, a family reading-visibility page (/guardian/reading), and
  cross-family connection consent (/guardian/connections, ADR-016)), <b>Admin</b>
  (the ADR-005 approval gate; the admin console also holds the master library
  (#277), user management, the authoring queue, the moderation dashboard/
  thresholds, the provider allowlist, and the audit log -- see sitemap-and-flows),
  <b>System</b> (generation + safety, behind the scenes).
  ADR-014: one AdultGate at the root of the whole adult subtree (not a per-page
  gate) is the single kid-to-adult boundary; step-up fires only crossing UP from
  kid mode, never guardian<->guardian, guardian<->admin, or admin<->guardian.
  See journey-kid for the child side, seq-device-grant for the device-grant
  mechanics, and journey-dev-coverage for test coverage.
endlegend

@enduml
